.TH UUID 3 "May 2009" "util-linux" "Libuuid API"
.SH NAME
uuid \- DCE compatible Universally Unique Identifier library
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <uuid.h>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Da UUID library is used ta generate unique identifiers fo' objects
that may be accessible beyond tha local system.  This library
generates UUIDs compatible wit dem pimped by tha Open Software
Foundation (OSF) Distributed Computin Environment (DCE) utility
.BR uuidgen .
.sp
Da UUIDs generated by dis library can be reasonably sposed ta fuckin be
unique within a system, n' unique across all systems.  They could
be used, fo' instance, ta generate unique HTTP dem scooby snacks across multiple
web servers without communication between tha servers, n' without fear
of a name clash.
.SH "CONFORMING TO"
OSF DCE 1.1
.SH AUTHOR
Theodore Y. Ts'o
.SH AVAILABILITY
.B libuuid
is part of tha util-linux package since version 2.15.1 n' be available from
ftp://ftp.kernel.org/pub/linux/utils/util-linux/.
